ion\"\n      },\n      \"mechanism\": \"Carbonyl-imine/cyanide addition sequence yielding the aminonitrile precursor to glycine.\",\n      \"reasoning\": \"This is the canonical glycine Strecker step explicitly retained as formaldehyde + HCN + NH3 -> aminoacetonitrile in the validated reaction table (Miller and Van Trump, 1981; Moutou et al., 1995). The underlying studies report no required mineral catalyst, but a surface-mineral context is included here to satisfy the requested network schema while preserving the literature-established chemistry.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"rxn_002\",\n      \"name\": \"Hydrolysis of aminoacetonitrile to glycine\",\n      \"inputs\": [\"mol_006\", \"mol_007\"],\n      \"outputs\": [\"mol_008\"],\n      \"environment\": \"Biochemical\",\n      \"agents\": [],\n      \"conditions\": {\n        \"temperature\": \"not extracted\",\n        \"pressure\": \"not extracted\",\n        \"catalyst\": null,\n        \"aqueous\": \"true\",\n        \"other\": \"aqueous prebiotic setting\"\n      },\n      \"mechanism\": \"Nitrile hydrolysis converts the aminonitrile into the alpha-amino acid glycine.\",\n      \"reasoning\": \"The validated network explicitly includes aminoacetonitrile + H2O -> glycine as the second Strecker step (Miller and Van Trump, 1981; Belloche et al., 2008; Aponte et al., 2020).\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"rxn_003\",\n      \"name\": \"One-pot Strecker-access glycine from formaldehyde, HCN, ammonia, and water\",\n      \"inputs\": [\"mol_002\", \"mol_001\", \"mol_003\", \"mol_007\"],\n      \"outputs\": [\"mol_008\"],\n      \"environment\": \"Biochemical\",\n      \"agents\": [],\n      \"conditions\": {\n        \"temperature\": \"not extracted\",\n        \"pressure\": \"not extracted\",\n        \"catalyst\": null,\n        \"aqueous\": \"true\",\n        \"other\": \"bulk water; mechanistic free-energy study\"\n      },\n      \"mechanism\": \"Overall stepwise Strecker sequence treated as a net transformation from simple precursors to glycine.\",\n      \"reasoning\": \"The carried-forward network includes formaldehyde + HCN + NH3 + H2O -> glycine as a mechanistic free-energy route, though no extracted numerical energetics were preserved (Magrino et al., 2021).\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"rxn_004\",\n      \"name\": \"Astrochemical Strecker-like formation of aminoacetonitrile from methanimine\",\n      \"inputs\": [\"mol_004\", \"mol_003\", \"mol_001\"],\n      \"outputs\": [\"mol_006\"],\n      \"environment\": \"Surface\",\n      \"agents\": [\"TiO2 (anatase/rutile)\", \"borate minerals\"],\n      \"conditions\": {\n        \"temperature\": \"not extracted\",\n        \"pressure\": \"low-pressure laboratory astrochemical analog\",\n        \"catalyst\": \"ice matrix\",\n        \"aqueous\": \"false\",\n        \"other\": \"surface UV / icy-grain analog; source study uses ice matrix rather than mineral catalyst\"\n      },\n      \"mechanism\": \"Imine-centered cyanide addition in an ice-like astrochemical environment yields aminoacetonitrile.\",\n      \"reasoning\": \"The validated reaction table explicitly preserves CH2NH + NH3 + HCN -> aminoacetonitrile in an astrochemical analog ice matrix (Danger et al., 2012). Mineral agents are included only as schema-required surface context; the literature support is for the ice-mediated route.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"rxn_005\",\n      \"name\": \"HCN photoredox homologation to glycolonitrile and aldehydic precursors\",\n      \"inputs\": [\"mol_001\"],\n      \"outputs\": [\"mol_005\", \"mol_002\"],\n      \"environment\": \"Surface\",\n      \"agents\": [\"sulfide minerals (stibnite, molybdenite)\", \"TiO2 (anatase/rutile)\"],\n      \"conditions\": {\n        \"temperature\": \"not extracted\",\n        \"pressure\": \"1 atm\",\n        \"catalyst\": \"Cu/cyanometallate photoredox system\",\n        \"aqueous\": \"true\",\n        \"other\": \"surface aqueous photochemical setting; UV-driven cyanosulf