).\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"rxn_016\",\n      \"name\": \"Glycine conversion to glycinamide-derived activated oligomerization pool\",\n      \"inputs\": [\"mol_006\"],\n      \"outputs\": [\"mol_021\"],\n      \"environment\": \"Biochemical\",\n      \"agents\": [],\n      \"conditions\": {\n        \"temperature\": \"prebiotic cycling conditions; exact temperature not preserved\",\n        \"pressure\": \"1 atm\",\n        \"catalyst\": null,\n        \"aqueous\": \"true\",\n        \"other\": \"prebiotic cycling environment; derivative/activated intermediate context\"\n      },\n      \"mechanism\": \"Glycine enters an activated amide derivative pool represented by glycinamide, which supports subsequent peptide-related chemistry.\",\n      \"reasoning\": \"The validated source base retains glycinamide as a glycine-related derivative and peptide-linked intermediate class. This node is included to connect target glycine to derivative activation chemistry without overstating an unsupported direct synthesis role. Supported context from Yanagawa et al. (1984) and Alonso et al. (2018).\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"rxn_017\",\n      \"name\": \"Negative test of de novo glycine synthesis from CO2 on FeS/H2S\",\n      \"inputs\": [\"mol_009\", \"mol_019\", \"mol_020\"],\n      \"outputs\": [],\n      \"environment\": \"Hydrothermal\",\n      \"agents\": [\"mackinawite (FeS)\", \"pyrite (FeS2)\"],\n      \"conditions\": {\n        \"temperature\": \"tested hydrothermal iron-sulfur conditions; exact temperature not preserved\",\n        \"pressure\": \"hydrothermal\",\n        \"catalyst\": \"FeS / FeS2-related system\",\n        \"aqueous\": \"true\",\n        \"other\": \"iron-sulfur world / hydrothermal critical test; no amino-acid production observed\"\n      },\n      \"mechanism\": \"Control/critical test showing failure of the proposed FeS/H2S de novo route to generate glycine under examined conditions.\",\n      \"reasoning\": \"The literature-guided instructions require following contradictions in the evidence base. The validated network explicitly preserves CO2 + FeS/H2S -> glycine as a key negative result reporting no amino-acid production. It is included here as a non-productive hydrothermal branch to prevent unsupported positive FeS claims. Supported by Keefe et al. (1995).\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"pathways\": [\n    {\n      \"pathway_id\": \"P1\",\n      \"name\": \"Classical two-step Strecker route\",\n      \"description\": \"Canonical aqueous Strecker synthesis from formaldehyde, HCN, and NH3 via aminoacetonitrile, followed by hydrolysis to glycine.\",\n      \"reaction_sequence\": [\"rxn_001\", \"rxn_002\"],\n      \"key_intermediates\": [\"mol_004\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"pathway_id\": \"P2\",\n      \"name\": \"Integrated one-pot Strecker route\",\n      \"description\": \"Mechanistically studied direct access to glycine from formaldehyde, HCN, NH3, and water in a single integrated Strecker sequence.\",\n      \"reaction_sequence\": [\"rxn_003\"],\n      \"key_intermediates\": [\"mol_001\", \"mol_002\", \"mol_003\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"pathway_id\": \"P3\",\n      \"name\": \"Astrochemical methanimine Strecker-like route\",\n      \"description\": \"Methanimine in icy astrochemical settings reacts with NH3 and HCN to form aminoacetonitrile, which hydrolyzes to glycine.\",\n      \"reaction_sequence\": [\"rxn_004\", \"rxn_002\"],\n      \"key_intermediates\": [\"mol_007\", \"mol_004\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"pathway_id\": \"P4\",\n      \"name\": \"Cyanosulfidic alpha-aminonitrile route\",\n      \"description\": \"HCN/HS-/UV/Cu photoredox chemistry accesses alpha-aminonitrile precursor space including aminoacetonitrile, which then hydrolyzes to glycine.\",\n      \"reaction_sequence\": [\"rxn_006\", \"rxn_002\"],\n      \"key_intermediates\": [\"mol_004\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"pathway_id\": \"P5\",\n      \"name\": \"HCN homologation through glycolonitrile-accessible precursor space\",\n      \"description\": \"HCN photoredox homologation yields glycolonitrile and formaldehyde precursor pools; glycolonitrile then enters aqueous Strecker-adjacent chemistry to access aminoacetonitrile and glycine.\",\n      \"reaction_sequence\": [\"rxn_005\", \"rxn_007\"],\n      \"key_intermediates\": [\"mol_008\", \"mol_001\", \"mol_004\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"pathway_id\": \"P6\",\n      \"name\": \"Formamide-linked aminonitrile route\",\n      \"description\": \"Formamide-mediated aldehyde/cyanide chemistry yields aminoacetonitrile and N-formylaminonitriles; aminoacetonitrile hydrolyzes to glycine.\",\n      \"reaction_sequence\": [\"rxn_013\", \"rxn_002\"],\n      \"key_intermediates\": [\"mol_014\", \"mol_015\", \"mol_004\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"pathway_id\": \"P7\",\n      \"name\": \"Direct UV-ice methylamine plus CO2 route\",\n      \"description\": \"UV irradiation of H2O/CH3NH2/CO2 ice films directly forms glycine.\",\n      \"reaction_sequence\": [\"rxn_008\"],\n      \"key_intermediates\": [\"mol_009\", \"mol_010\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"pathway_id\": \"P8\",\n      \"name\": \"Realistic interstellar ice mixture route\",\n      \"description\": \"UV irradiation of realistic cometary/interstellar mixed ices yields glycine directly.\",\n      \"reaction_sequence\": [\"rxn_009\"],\n      \"key_intermediates\": [\"mol_009\", \"mol_002\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"pathway_id\": \"P9\",\n      \"name\": \"Alkaline hydrothermal ethanolamine route\",\n      \"description\": \"Ethanolamine is converted to glycine in alkaline hydrothermal vent simulation with metal powders.\",\n      \"reaction_sequence\": [\"rxn_010\"],\n      \"key_intermediates\": [\"mol_011\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"pathway_id\": \"P10\",\n      \"name\": \"Ferroan brucite glyoxylate route\",\n      \"description\": \"Glyoxylate and nitrate yield glycine directly on ferroan brucite in a geochemically plausible mineral setting.\",\n      \"reaction_sequence\": [\"rxn_012\"],\n      \"key_intermediates\": [\"mol_012\", \"mol_013\"]\n    }\n  ],\n  \"hub_molecules\": [\"mol_002\", \"mol_001\", \"mol_004\", \"mol_006\", \"mol_009\"],\n  \"convergence_points\": [\n    {\n      \"molecule_id\": \"mol_004\",\n      \"incoming_reactions\": [\"rxn_001\", \"rxn_004\", \"rxn_006\", \"rxn_007\", \"rxn_013\"],\n      \"outgoing_reactions\": [\"rxn_002\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"molecule_id\": \"mol_006\",\n      \"incoming_reactions\": [\"rxn_002\", \"rxn_003\", \"rxn_007\", \"rxn_008\", \"rxn_009\", \"rxn_010\", \"rxn_011\", \"rxn_012\"],\n      \"outgoing_reactions\": [\"rxn_014\", \"rxn_015\", \"rxn_016\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"molecule_id\": \"mol_001\",\n      \"incoming_reactions\": [\"rxn_005\"],\n      \"outgoing_reactions\": [\"rxn_001\", \"rxn_003\", \"rxn_013\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"molecule_id\": \"mol_002\",\n      \"incoming_reactions\": [],\n      \"outgoing_reactions\": [\"rxn_001\", \"rxn_003\", \"rxn_004\", \"rxn_005\", \"rxn_006\", \"rxn_009\", \"rxn_013\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"molecule_id\": \"mol_009\",\n      \"incoming_reactions\": [],\n      \"outgoing_reactions\": [\"rxn_008\", \"rxn_009\", \"rxn_011\", \"rxn_017\"]\n    }\n  ]\n}", "parsed_response": {"target_molecule": "Glycine", "overall_strategy": "This network targets glycine through ten literature-grounded, convergent prebiotic routes centered on four major hubs: HCN, formaldehyde, aminoacetonitrile, and glycine, with CO2 as an additional cross-environment feedstock hub. The design follows the validated evidence base: classical Strecker synthesis and hydrolysis; astrochemical Strecker-like aminoacetonitrile formation from methanimine; cyanosulfidic photoredox access to aldehydic and aminonitrile precursor pools without overstating unsupported direct steps; direct UV-ice glycine formation from CH3NH2/CO2/H2O and from realistic ice mixtures; hydrothermal ethanolamine conversion under alkaline vent simulation; contested but retained vent-like glycine generation from simple hydrothermal feedstocks; and the mineral-mediated glyoxylate+nitrate+ferroan brucite route. Downstream reactions include iron-sulfur mediated peptide activation and hydrothermal oligomerization to connect synthesis to biochemical emergence. Negative FeS/H2S de novo evidence is explicitly included as a cautionary, non-productive hydrothermal branch so the network reflects the literature contradiction rather than inventing an unsupported positive route.", "molecules": [{"id": "mol_001", "formula": "CH2O", "iupac_name": "methanal", "common_name": "formaldehyde", "inchi": "InChI=1S/CH2O/c1-2/h1H2", "role": "hub_intermediate", "environment_formed": "Surface"}, {"id": "mol_002", "formula": "HCN", "iupac_name": "hydrogen cyanide", "common_name": "HCN", "inchi": "InChI=1S/CHN/c1-2/h1H", "role": "hub_intermediate", "environment_formed": "Surface"}, {"id": "mol_003", "formula": "H3N", "iupac_name": "azane", "common_name": "ammonia", "inchi": "InChI=1S/H3N/h1H3", "role": "hub_intermediate", "environment_formed": null}, {"id": "mol_004", "formula": "C2H4N2", "iupac_name": "2-aminoacetonitrile", "common_name": "aminoacetonitrile", "inchi": "InChI=1S/C2H4N2/c3-1-2-4/h2H,3H2", "role": "hub_intermediate", "environment_formed": "Surface"}, {"id": "mol_005", "formula": "H2O", "iupac_name": "oxidane", "common_name": "water", "inchi": "InChI=1S/H2O/h1H2", "role": "starting", "environment_formed": null}, {"id": "mol_006", "formula": "C2H5NO2", "iupac_name": "aminoacetic acid", "common_name": "glycine", "inchi": "InChI=1S/C2H5NO2/c3-1-2(4)5/h1,3H2,(H,4,5)", "role": "target", "environment_formed": "Biochemical"}, {"id": "mol_007", "formula": "CH3N", "iupac_name": "methanimine", "common_name": "methanimine", "inchi": "InChI=1S/CH3N/c1-2/h1H,2H2", "role": "intermediate", "environment_formed": "Surface"}, {"id": "mol_008", "formula": "C2H3NO", "iupac_name": "2-hydroxyacetonitrile", "common_name": "glycolonitrile", "inchi": "InChI=1S/C2H3NO/c3-1-2-4/h4H,2H2", "role": "hub_intermediate", "environment_f