nce >= 0.9\n\nOutput your evaluation as JSON matching the NetworkEvaluation schema.\n", "user_message": "Evaluate this synthesis network:\n\nTARGET MOLECULE: Glycine\nOVERALL STRATEGY: This network targets glycine through ten literature-grounded, convergent prebiotic routes centered on four major hubs: HCN, formaldehyde, aminoacetonitrile, and glycine, with CO2 as an additional cross-environment feedstock hub. The design follows the validated evidence base: classical Strecker synthesis and hydrolysis; astrochemical Strecker-like aminoacetonitrile formation from methanimine; cyanosulfidic photoredox access to aldehydic and aminonitrile precursor pools without overstating unsupported direct steps; direct UV-ice glycine formation from CH3NH2/CO2/H2O and from realistic ice mixtures; hydrothermal ethanolamine conversion under alkaline vent simulation; contested but retained vent-like glycine generation from simple hydrothermal feedstocks; and the mineral-mediated glyoxylate+nitrate+ferroan brucite route. Downstream reactions include iron-sulfur mediated peptide activation and hydrothermal oligomerization to connect synthesis to biochemical emergence. Negative FeS/H2S de novo evidence is explicitly included as a cautionary, non-productive hydrothermal branch so the network reflects the literature contradiction rather than inventing an unsupported positive route.\n\nMOLECULES (21 nodes):\n  - mol_001: CH2O (formaldehyde) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_002: HCN (HCN) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_003: H3N (ammonia) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_004: C2H4N2 (aminoacetonitrile) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_005: H2O (water) [starting]\n  - mol_006: C2H5NO2 (glycine) [target]\n  - mol_007: CH3N (methanimine) [intermediate]\n  - mol_008: C2H3NO (glycolonitrile) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_009: CO2 (carbon dioxide) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_010: CH5N (methylamine) [intermediate]\n  - mol_011: C2H7NO (ethanolamine) [intermediate]\n  - mol_012: C2H2O3 (glyoxylic acid) [intermediate]\n  - mol_013: HNO3 (nitrate) [starting]\n  - mol_014: CH3NO (formamide) [intermediate]\n  - mol_015: C2H3N3O (N-formylaminonitrile) [intermediate]\n  - mol_016: HS- (hydrosulfide) [starting]\n  - mol_017: C4H8N2O3 (diglycine) [intermediate]\n  - mol_018: CO (carbon monoxide) [starting]\n  - mol_019: FeS (mackinawite/FeS) [starting]\n  - mol_020: H2S (hydrogen sulfide) [starting]\n  - mol_021: C2H5NO (glycinamide) [intermediate]\n\nREACTIONS (17 nodes):\n  - rxn_001: mol_001, mol_002, mol_003 -> mol_004 (Classical Strecker formation of aminoacetonitrile from formaldehyde) [Surface]\n  - rxn_002: mol_004, mol_005 -> mol_006 (Hydrolysis of aminoacetonitrile to glycine) [Biochemical]\n  - rxn_003: mol_001, mol_002, mol_003, mol_005 -> mol_006 (One-pot Strecker access to glycine from formaldehyde, HCN, NH3, and water) [Biochemical]\n  - rxn_004: mol_007, mol_003, mol_002 -> mol_004 (Astrochemical Strecker-like formation of aminoacetonitrile from methanimine) [Surface]\n  - rxn_005: mol_002, mol_005 -> mol_008, mol_001 (HCN photoredox homologation to glycolonitrile and formaldehyde precursor pool) [Surface]\n  - rxn_006: mol_002, mol_016, mol_003 -> mol_004 (Cyanosulfidic photoredox access to alpha-aminonitrile precursor pool including aminoacetonitrile) [Surface]\n  - rxn_007: mol_008, mol_003, mol_005 -> mol_004, mol_006 (Glycolonitrile conversion to glycine-related intermediate pool) [Biochemical]\n  - rxn_008: mol_005, mol_010, mol_009 -> mol_006 (Direct UV-ice glycine synthesis from methylamine and carbon dioxide) [Surface]\n  - rxn_009: mol_005, mol_009, mol_003, mol_010, mol_002 -> mol_006 (UV irradiation of realistic interstellar/cometary ice mixtures to glycine) [Surface]\n  - rxn_010: mol_011 -> mol_006 (Alkaline hydrothermal vent conversion of ethanolamine to glycine) [Hydrothermal]\n  - rxn_011: mol_009, mol_003, mol_005 -> mol_006 (Vent-like hydrothermal formation of glycine from simple feedstocks) [Hydrothermal]\n  - rxn_012: mol_012, mol_013 -> mol_006 (Mineral